  "prompt": "How much time does HSBC take to provide offer letter?",
  "response": "The time it takes for HSBC (or any company) to provide an offer letter can vary depending on several factors, including the specific role, the number of candidates being considered, the internal processes of the company, and the time of year. On average, it might take anywhere from a few days to a few weeks after the final interview, as they usually need to finalize details and conduct any remaining background checks.\n\nFor the most accurate information, it's best to directly inquire with the HR representative or recruiter at HSBC who is managing your application. They should be able to give you a clearer timeline based on their current workload and processes.",
